      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "An objective researcher must rigorously control for confounding variables to address this claim. They would employ quantitative methods to statistically isolate socioeconomic factors, policing intensity, and historical context from reported group behaviors. Furthermore, qualitative research can examine cultural norms to see how they interact with, rather than solely cause, contact with the law. Ultimately, an objective analysis must demonstrate causation beyond correlation, acknowledging how systemic inputs shape the outcomes observed.",
      "source": "target",
